sharedPost.text:
Alternate Shadows performed `Screaming Blue Murder' at Gillingham Golf Club last night to a sold out house for Halloween. We shall be performing `Screaming Blue Murder!' again one more time at Sheerness Golf Club - 7pm!

It's 1974 Frank Wagenheim’s new movie ‘Fanghelsing’ is the hot topic of tinsel town – although screen idol, Max Brant & co-star Daisy White are tipped for top honours, there’s a chilling atmosphere on set that has nothing to do with it being over budget and over schedule!

Filming on location at Moreham Wood Film Studios, on the set of a crypt in a decaying abbey, Inspector Grimpole finds the blood is more than just special effects and the screams are not just in the script!

**Don't be a blood sucker and reserve your ticket - Tickets are £5 and can be obtained by calling the golf club on 01795 662585. **

The evening will be nothing short of fang-tastic!

Sehr geehrte Damen und Herren,

 ich suche eine Ausbildung als Köchin in Deutschland. Ich habe bereits Erfahrung in diesem Bereich, koche sehr gerne und habe große Freude daran, neue Gerichte zuzubereiten.

 Haben Sie vielleicht einen freien Ausbildungsplatz?

 Gerne sende ich Ihnen meinen Lebenslauf und weitere Unterlagen zu.

 Mit freundlichen Grüßen
Imane

Nowy program dokumentalny jednej z topowych stacji telewizyjnych szuka byłych i emerytowanych policjantów – ludzi z doświadczeniem, charakterem i prawdziwymi historiami.

🎬 Wystąpisz jako prowadzący oraz w scenach inscenizujących zatrzymania, interwencje i działania policyjne.

📅 Zdjęcia odbędą się pod koniec roku i potrwają około 3 miesięcy.

To wyjątkowa okazja, by pokazać kulisy policyjnej pracy i przywrócić emocje służby – tym razem przed kamerą!

👉 Zgłoś się tutaj: https://shortaudition.com/Aplikuj

🎥 Nagraj krótką wizytówkę wideo i opowiedz kilka słów o sobie — dodaj nagranie w zakładce Video.

Perfect for anyone who makes TikToks/Reels already and wants a quick gig.

📩 Contact: info@cbexldn.com

items.text:
**Szukam modelki na zasadzie TFP  Gliwice/Katowice ( Śląsk )  **

 

   Szukam pań które nie krępują się własnego ciała i chciałaby mieć ciekawą pamiątkę w postaci klimatycznych zdjęć.  Wiem jak bardzo jest ważna akceptacja własnego ciała bo przez to też możemy inaczej funkcjonować. Przez takie zdjęcia można również tego dokonać. Sesja w głównej mierze jest jako taki motywator.

 

Poszukuje kobiety w **wieku od 30 **lat nie koniecznie z doświadczeniem pozowania,  na zasadach Tfp mieszkającej w Gliwicach lub okolicach Zabrze czy Katowice najdalej. Posiadam na wyposażeniu mini studio z kilkoma tłami oraz lampami. Mam również duży wybór kostiumów i gadżetów do wykorzystywania. Główny motyw do kobieta: Piękna i drapieżna! Sama sesja trwa przeważnie od 1,5h do 2h w zalezności od motywów.

** **

**Temat 1 – ‘’Kobieta mafii 1930’’**

Postać kobiety osadzona w 1930 roku w roli bogatej kobiety, która trudni się gangsterstwem. Przewidziane są ujęcia m.in. przy stoliku na którym są pieniądze, wino, rewolwer. Tło jest wydrukowane w formie muru, cegieł. Motyw sensualny.

 

**Temat 2 – ‘’Wampirzyca w baroku 1700’’**

Postać kobiety ubrana najpierw w suknie czarną oraz peleryne z kapturem. Do tego czarna długa peruka oraz czarne paznokcie. W kolejnym etapie sesji motyw sensualny.

 

**Temat 3 – ‘’Duchy lasu’’**

Postać kobiety ubrana w wianek i w pelerynę z otwartym przodem. W dłoni ma zakrwawiony sierp. Usta czarne oraz paznokcie.

 

https://www.maxmodels.pl/lukus_wielki2

**Zapraszam na stronę Facebook Łukasz Magiera – Fotografia**

 

Więcej informacji na Priv

items.text:
Agencja Statystów Merito z WFDiF w Warszawie

poszukuje grupy 20 statystów w wieku 25-50 lat

do nagrań reklamy Leku w piątek (07.11.2025)

Będą nagrywane sceny w autobusie miejskim,

nagrania będą w Warszawie dlatego z powodów logistycznych

rozpatrywane będą osoby z Warszawy i okolic.

Trzeba sobie zarezerwować całą dniówkę bo nie wiemy ile to dokładnie potrwa.

Nagrania mogą potrwać cały dzień, od rana do nocy,

zwyczajowo plan filmowy trwa 12 godzin i na tyle należy być dyspozycyjnym w przypadku zgłoszenia.

W kolejnym tygodniu wybranym osobom podamy szczegóły zbiórki na plan

Wynagrodzenie jak za statystowanie w reklamie,

dokładną wysokość podamy po zgłoszeniu na maila.

Zainteresowane osoby, mieszkające tylko i wyłącznie w Warszawie (bo w Warszawie jest nagranie)

prosimy o zgłoszenie na maila:

casting@agencjamerito.pl

w temacie maila prosimy wpisać: LEK

W załączniku do maila prosimy o kilka twoich zdjęć ( portret, sylwetka, ważące najlepiej do 200kb, na których widać Cię w sposób prawdziwy, bez okularów, itp.) zgłoszenia z cięższymi zdjęciami mogą do nas nie dotrzeć.

Prosimy o podanie w treści maila:

- Imię i nazwisko

- data urodzenia

- czy mieszkasz w Warszawie?

- czy jest się dostępnym na cały 07.11.2025?

- prosimy podać numer telefonu

- informację czy jest się zarejestrowanym w bazie naszej agencji

Pasujące osoby do tego statystowania które są już u nas zarejestrowane dostały już od nas dziś informację.

Prosimy o zgłoszenia do Piątku (31.10) do godz. 12 to wyślemy zdjęcia do produkcji,

Następnie będziemy informować wybrane przez produkcję osoby.

Zespół Merito

www.agencjamerito.pl

items.text:
**Trójmiasto / Kołobrzeg**

Termin: najbliższy piątek (31.10)

Firma dla której nagrywam materiały potrzebuje aktora/modela (mężczyznę) - kogoś kto czuje się dobrze przed kamerą i ważne - umie się swobodnie wypowiadać. Będą to nagrania pod rolki - tekst przygotowany i wyświetlany będzie na prompterze. Ponadto nagrania obejmują również przebitki typowo z hali produkcyjnej, techniczne zagadnienia itd. 

**Lokalizacja:**

Nagrania odbywają się w **Kołobrzegu**, ale oferuję wyjazd z **Gdańska** jeszcze w nocy, tak żeby być na miejscu około godziny 9 w piątek. Także proszę o zgłoszenie się osób, które mają dostępny calutki piątek. Albo osoby na miejscu w Kołobrzegu (same nagrania trwać będą około 8-9 godzin).

Kwota: **700 zł płatne od razu po planie.**

Pola eksploatacji: social media.

Zgłoszenia na: **yokan.std@gmail.com**

Tytuł maila: CASTING - KOŁOBRZEG - ROLKI

**W treści: **imię, nazwisko, wiek, wzrost, numer telefonu, aktualne zdjęcie twarzy oraz aktualne zdjęcie całej sylwetki.

**+ Najważniejsze** - próbkę Waszej wypowiedzi. Nawet może być nagrane telefonem. Najlepiej wrzuć ten film na Youtube (niepubliczny link) i podeślij link do niego. Zrób 2. wariacje - 1. wersja: 20 sekund jakiejś profesjonalnej wypowiedzi z branży technicznej, cokolwiek. Spokojny łagodny ton. 2. wersja: 20 sekund dynamicznej a'la vlogowej luźnej wypowiedzi.

Nagrania odbywają się w **Kołobrzegu**, ale oferuję wyjazd z **Gdańska** jeszcze w nocy, tak żeby być na miejscu około godziny 9 w piątek. Także proszę o zgłoszenie się osób, które mają dostępny calutki piątek. Albo osoby na miejscu w Kołobrzegu (same nagrania trwać będą około 8-9 godzin).

Kwota: **700 zł płatne od razu po planie.**

Pola eksploatacji: social media.

Zgłoszenia na: **yokan.std@gmail.com**

Tytuł maila: CASTING - KOŁOBRZEG - ROLKI

**W treści: **imię, nazwisko, wiek, wzrost, numer telefonu, aktualne zdjęcie twarzy oraz aktualne zdjęcie całej sylwetki.

**+ Najważniejsze** - próbkę Waszej wypowiedzi. Nawet może być nagrane telefonem. Najlepiej wrzuć ten film na Youtube (niepubliczny link) i podeślij link do niego. Zrób 2. wariacje - 1. wersja: 20 sekund jakiejś profesjonalnej wypowiedzi z branży technicznej, cokolwiek. Spokojny łagodny ton. 2. wersja: 20 sekund dynamicznej a'la vlogowej luźnej wypowiedzi.
items.title: **Trójmiasto / Kołobrzeg**

sharedPost.text:
Nowy program dokumentalny jednej z topowych stacji telewizyjnych szuka byłych i emerytowanych policjantów – ludzi z doświadczeniem, charakterem i prawdziwymi historiami.

🎬 Wystąpisz jako prowadzący oraz w scenach inscenizujących zatrzymania, interwencje i działania policyjne.

📅 Zdjęcia odbędą się pod koniec roku i potrwają około 3 miesięcy.

To wyjątkowa okazja, by pokazać kulisy policyjnej pracy i przywrócić emocje służby – tym razem przed kamerą!

👉 Zgłoś się tutaj: https://shortaudition.com/Aplikuj

🎥 Nagraj krótką wizytówkę wideo i opowiedz kilka słów o sobie — dodaj nagranie w zakładce Video.

# Statist*innen für neues YouTube-Dating-Format gesucht!

Was sagt der TikTok-Feed über uns aus? Kann man darüber entscheiden, ob man eine Person daten möchte oder nicht?

Für ein neues YouTube-Dating-Format sind wir auf der Suche nach Kandidat*innen und einem Moderator, die herausfinden wollen, wie aussagekräftig der TikTok-Algorithmus für potentielle Dating-Partner*innen ist.

Du schaust gerne TikToks, und du hast kein Problem damit, deinen Feed offenzulegen? Dann bewirb dich als Kandidat*in!

Bewirb dich jetzt als Single – wir bewerten den TikTok Feed gemeinsam, du triffst deine Entscheidung!

Zeitraum: 7. + 8.11. (du musst nur an einem der beiden Drehtage Zeit haben)

Ort: Köln

130 € Aufwandsentschädigung, Reisekostenpauschale nach Absprache

Bewerbungslink: [[https://wkf.ms/3J0Xqtn](https://wkf.ms/3J0Xqtn)](https://wkf.ms/3J0Xqtn)

Bei Fragen, melde dich gerne unter casting@33minutes.de

items.text:
🎬** Medvirkende søges til kortfilm for **Foreningen Lige Adgang

I forbindelse med mit speciale, udvikler jeg en række **kortfilm i samarbejde med Foreningen Lige Adgang**, der vises som en del af deres workshops og oplæg om **antidiskrimination **– optagelser i København.

Vi søger medvirkende, der vil dele deres perspektiver – **uanset om du har etnisk minoritetsbaggrund eller er allieret**, som vil bidrage til en vigtig samtale om trivsel, inklusion og ligestilling.

Du **behøver ingen filmisk erfaring** – kun lyst til at bidrage til en vigtig samtale.

Det vigtigste er, at du har lyst til at dele dine tanker eller erfaringer og være med til at skabe film, der kan gøre en forskel.

**Fokus på tryghed og inkluderende deltagelse:**
* Filmene udvikles gennem workshops, hvor du som deltager har **medindflydelse og ejerskab** over processen og fortællingen
* Vi arbejder med **løbende samtykke**, og du godkender altid materialet, før noget deles
* **Alle medvirkende krediteres som medskabere** i filmen 🎬

Temaer, vi arbejder med:
💬 Hvad vil det sige at være en god allieret?
🔄 Hvad hvis rollerne var byttet om?
👥 Oplevelser af inklusion og eksklusion
🧠 Fordomme og bias i hverdagen

**Praktisk:**
📍 København – start/midt november 2025 (fleksibelt ud fra din kalender)
🕒 To hele dage (ca. 6–7 timer pr. dag) – mulighed for én dag eller en halv dag
🥗 Forplejning er inkluderet

Vi ønsker et **mangfoldigt cast **og opfordrer alle til at melde sig – uanset køn, seksualitet, alder, etnicitet, religion, faglig baggrund eller funktionsevne.

Skriv til mig via **malene.juell@gmail.com** eller en direkte besked med:
* Hvilke(n) dag(e) i november, du bedst kan
* Gerne et billede af dig selv

—

**Malene Juell-Hansen** (specialestuderende på Film- og medievidenskab, Københavns Universitet)

I samarbejde med Foreningen Lige Adgang

📢 **OBS: Opslaget må gerne deles** – kender du nogen, der kunne være interesseret, må du meget gerne videresende opslaget!

items.text:
**"SKJOLD" - CASTING CALL**

**KBH Film- & Fotoskole**

Hvis du er interesseret i en af rollerne, må du gerne sende en mail til:

**skjoldfilm@gmail.com**

Vi søger 3 mandlige skuespillere til vores afgangsfilm “Skjold”. **Optagelser foregår fra d. 17/11-25/11.** 

Skjold og Lou går til kampsport og er bedste venner. Men da Skjold møder den anderledes, mystiske Mikkel, opstår der uventede følelser og reaktioner i Skjolds’ krop. Lou begynder at fatte mistanke, mens de nærmer sig finalen i turneringen hvor Skjold og Lou skal slås.

**SKJOLD (Hovedkarakter)**

Tilbageholdende medløber. Ikke en af dem der råber højest, men vil gerne være en af drengene. I konflikt med sig selv, og føler hans krop forråder ham. 

**LOU**

Dominerende, drilsk og overlegen. Bruger kampsport som en rustning, mod sin far og omverdenen.

**MIKKEL**

Mystisk, feminin og tvetydig. Udfordrer Skjolds fordomme om verdenen og maskulinitet og afslører hans usikkerhed.

På forhånd tak,

William Devantier

Producer

Late November/early December Shoot (date tbd)

 

To play the villain in an Intense Crime Drama short.

 

Description: London-based, Male, White, , playing age 25 - 35, Athletic, 5'10+, 80 kg+, with experience playing strong character roles on stage or screen.

 

£300 for 1-Day-Shoot plus half a day of rehearsals.

 

Please send in a cover letter with your resume with headshot and your showreel to Davina Brown at k2filmworksgmail.com Please do not respond in the comments or via DM.

🎞🎞 TRAIN WITH US 🎞🎞 

https://www.eventbrite.com/e/screen-acting-course-online-tickets-1880127334469?aff=oddtdtcreator 

STIRLING MANAGEMENT ACTORS AGENCY PRESENTS:

ACTING FOR SCREEN ONLINE INTENSIVE
A 14 HOUR NTENSIVE TRAINING PACKAGE DELIVERED TO YOU ONLINE ACROSS 7 MODULES - 2 HOURS EACH.

Modules:

Module One: Belief and Memory - MONDAY 17th NOVEMBER 18:30-20:30

Module Two: Emotions - TUESDAY 18th NOVEMBER 18:30-20:30

Module Three: Comedy - MONDAY 24th NOVEMBER 18:30-20:30

Module Four: Movement/Hotseating - TUESDAY 25th NOVEMBER 18:30-20:30

Module Five: Characterisation/Roleplay - MONDAY 1st DECEMBER 18:30-20:30

Module Six: Audition Techniques - TUESDAY 2nd DECEMBER 18:30-20:30

Module Seven: Self-Taping and Camera Work - SUNDAY 7th DECEMBER 18:30-20:30

WHAT TO EXPECT:

During these sessions you will work with both script and devised improvisation.

Woven throughout each module is insight to real industry knowledge

Our sessions will be 2 hours each

Skills Based hour

Devising and Performance hour

Feedback tailored to YOU is imperative within our course

Small cohorts allow each delegate the chance to have direct feedback tailored to them.

A Friendly, professional environment with zero judgment

Our sessions are taught by Stirling Management Actors Agency's - Artistic Director: Nathan Wedge

Your final session will also be observed by our Lead Talent Agent - Carly

Many of Stirling's past students have gone on to appear in TV Soaps, TV Series, Film and Commercial.

Book Now to avoid disappointment - FURTHER DATES WILL BE ANNOUNCED IN 2026.

SPECIAL PRICE: £70 + Booking Fee

(Gives you access to all 7 modules - works out to ONLY £5 per hour! )

Course Requirements:

Access to a computer with camera and microphone
Stable internet connection

Course Material:

All scripts that are to be used within the seven week course will be emailed to you clearly labelled which module they are for ahead of the course start date 17th November.

There is no need to learn the material sent, although if you want to familirise yourself with the content please do!

Who Can Join:
Open to all abilities

items.text:
Open casting for Spring Awakening! 

Off Topic are looking for creatives to join us in our new production of Frank Wedekind’s raw and revolutionary classic! We’re casting actors, looking for stage crew and other roles to join our exciting new project…if you’re interested please email offtopictheatre@hotmail.com to receive an application pack and register your place in our group workshop on 20th November 🌸

Lipa university - Liverpool - Thursday 20th November 7pm-9pm. Mount Street, Liverpool, L1 9HF

Paid on profit share basis - please note this is the play version not the musical 🎭

items.text:
🎭 Not your usual acting class

This Tuesday we explore what happens when there’s no partner, no dialogue, only you, the camera, and your thoughts.

Focus: The Living Monologue: From Performed Speech to Ongoing Experience
Learn to stay alive and reactive when alone on camera, to stop watching yourself and live the moment instead.

We’ll also dedicate part of the class to a Self-Tape Review. Bring one of your tapes and receive focused on-camera feedback on framing, emotional truth, and what the camera actually sees. It’s an opportunity to refine your presence, understand how your work reads on screen, and take your self-tapes to the next level.

Each Tuesday we explore a new topic through both psychological and on-camera perspectives, uncovering emotional truth, presence, and authenticity.

🗓 Tuesday November 4 at 7 PM
📍 Midtown Toronto
🎬 First class FREE for new actors

If this kind of work speaks to you, sign up here:
https://forms.gle/3LqxHGM9mfAvtaoa6

📽 IMDB: https://www.imdb.com/name/nm10480327/
📸 Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/isee.alina

items.summary:
🎭 Not your usual acting class

This Tuesday we explore what happens when there’s no partner, no dialogue, only you, the camera, and your thoughts.

Focus: The Living Monologue: From Performed Speech to Ongoing Experience
Learn to stay alive and reactive when alone on camera, to stop watching yourself and live the moment instead.

We’ll also dedicate part of the class to a Self-Tape Review. Bring one of your tapes and receive focused on-camera feedback on framing, emotional truth, and what the camera actually sees. It’s an opportunity to refine your presence, understand how your work reads on screen, and take your self-tapes to the next level.

Each Tuesday we explore a new topic through both psychological and on-camera perspectives, uncovering emotional truth, presence, and authenticity.

🗓 Tuesday November 4 at 7 PM
📍 Midtown Toronto
🎬 First class FREE for new actors

If this kind of work speaks to you, sign up here:
https://forms.gle/3LqxHGM9mfAvtaoa6

📽 IMDB: https://www.imdb.com/name/nm10480327/
📸 Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/isee.alina

Union / Non-Union: Non-Union
Production Type: Independent
Project length: Short film
Project format: 4:3
Production Company: JMA FILMS 
Director: Justin Adams
Audition Location: Video Audition
Shooting Location:  Wrightsville PA
Email: Filmmakerjustin@gmail.com
Compensation: Unpaid. Food and IMDb credit only.

Synopsis: A boy won't finish his milk and so the babysitter tells him a story about a not so kind milkman

Casting information: PLEASE READ 
Character Bios:

Resident's Wife(Support)Female 35-40. in the flashback scene from 50s

To be considered, you MUST send your CV/Resume to Filmmakerjustin@gmail.com. Do not use messenger. If you DO NOT reside in the DMV or York PA areas, we will not look at your submission unless you state you are willing to travel/lodge at your own expense. All actors will provide their own transportation.

The audition process:
1. Submit a resume or CV along with a head shot to Filmmakerjustin@gmail.com
2. Please state in the subject line the name of the character.
3. If selected, you will be given sides, instructions on how to submit, and a due date.
Any questions can be sent to the Filmmakerjustin@gmail.com email.

attachments.ocrText: May be a graphic of text that says 'JMA Films "It's It'sjustpureentertainment" just pure entertainment"'

topComments.text:
Unless it's a student production ALWAYS pay your cast and crew. Start a crowdfunding campaign, apply to advocacy groups that align with your film's message for grants, take out a personal bank loan, hold bake sales and car washes, meet with local/regional businesses for product placement.

Even Spike Lee, before he was "Spike Lee" got financing for his first film "She's Gotta Have It" when no one even knew who Spike Lee was..But STOP this practice of expecting Actors and Crew to work for free on your films.

What about liability insurance to cover the cast and crew on set? A film set is a place where a lot of incidents could happen. What if they get hurt on set? How are you going to compensate them for their medical expenses and lost work time? How are you going to cover equipment damaged or lost to such a situation? What if the property (house, offices, vase, etc. ) gets damaged, how are you going to cover those expenses?

What about a completion bond to insure the film is finished or pay the people for their time if it's not? Do you have that? 

My point is you have to start treating your business as a BUSINESS and stop expecting cast and crew to work for free. Filmmaking isn't just shooting footage on set and cutting it together in post. Part of filmmaking is finding the funding to make a film. And if you don't want to do that legwork then you don't really want to be in the film industry.

items.text:
SYNOPSIS: When granddaughter, Red, stops receiving letters from her sick grandmother she insists on visiting. Surprised, she finds a man who claims to be her grandmother’s new carer. As he continues to ask strange questions and refuses to let Red see her, she realises the man is taking advantage of her poor grandmother, using medicines to make her sicker. When confronted the man becomes enraged and is forced to kill little Red. 

Wanted: 2 actors (1 x M, 1 x F) for exciting new short film ‘In His Care’. Shooting in Hertfordshire, w/c 24th November, student project from an award-winning Film & TV course.

- RED (Female, 24 – 30)

- Description: Mid to late 20s

Red is a simple, reserved girl. She is kind and holds herself highly. But when it comes to her grandma, she is extremely protective, fierce even. She is perceptive and head strong and will do anything to find what’s happening at grandma’s house.

- Height: 5’5 – 5’9

- Appearance: Red is a modest girl. She dresses simple when visiting her grandmother, always wearing the infamous red scarf that her grandmother gave her.

- Pay Category: travel expenses and food covered

- HARRY (Male, 35 - 50)

- Description: Mid 30s to 50

Harry is carer to Ruth, conniving and manipulative; calculated and dominating. He knows what he wants and how to get it. He isn’t a smart perpetrator but rather simple-minded praying on those who can’t defend themselves and has no one to defend them. He has been getting away with it until a young girl with a fiery soul starts to uncover his secret.

Height: Tall (6ft approx.)

- Appearance: Harry is a seemingly ordinary guy on the outside. Charismatic, confident, tall, handsome, well kept. If you walked past him down the street, he may smile or wink at you. He uses his looks and caring façade as leverage.

- Pay category: travel expenses and food covered

If you’re interested, please submit showreels and any enquiries to sheldonkieran4@gmail.com by 7th November

items.text:
Hey there! 👋🏻😃

I’m Freya Tingley — an Australian actress born and raised in Perth. I started acting at 14, taking weekly classes with a dream of one day building a career in Hollywood.

Bit by bit, I booked short films, found a local agent, and put together a demo reel — all steps that helped me make the leap to LA just before turning 18. Not long after, I landed my first major role as a series regular on Netflix’s Hemlock Grove, followed by Once Upon a Time, Jersey Boys, and DOTA: Dragon’s Blood.

Of course, it wasn’t all smooth sailing and the journey had its pitfalls and huge learning curves along the way. But those ups and the downs gave me something valuable; an understanding of what works, what doesn’t and the exact steps to take to keep moving forward. 

Most acting schools don’t teach how to build a career — they’ll say “get an agent,” or “network: it’s all about who you know!” - but there’s never a clear road map, or step-by-step plan to help you to make progress, no matter where you’re at that.

I’m growing a community for actors who want a clear game plan, strategy, and support to level up and turn their goals into reality.

Come hang out with us! I’d love to meet you, hear your story, and help you move closer to your dreams.

👉 Join The Business of Acting www.skool.com/the-business-of-acting-9301/about?ref=387a46092b6b412b82c1a78a4c1a240e

See you there! 😃
— Freya

items.text:
Hi there, I’m a second year film student at METU directing a short scene for a class looking for a male actor! 

Longline: A relationship between a couple has reached its breaking point. However there is no hatred or malice between them, only a strong connection, pure love, and a melancholy understanding that they can no longer be together. 

Characters

Daisy is the female protagonist,  the scene mainly follows her view of her relationship with her long time partner Oliver. Daisy is a young adult photographer living with her partner who she deeply loves. 

Oliver is an accountant for a mid tier firm and is Daisys long time partner. They are not married but have been together for two years and he loves her deeply. After a serious disagreement between them the night before, he decides he can no longer be with Daisy despite feeling immense love for her. There is no malice or hatred, just release. 

Looking for an actor, playing age 20-25, to fill the male part

Date: 4th November

Location: Near Oktogon 

Time: 9:30-17:30

Compensation: Not paid (as it is a student project) but food and drinks will be provided 

Final film will be shared with the cast so it can be used for showreels or acting material. 

If you’re interested please reach out!☺️

Either through dm or email at kaliste.rodi@gmail.com

Be careful doing business with freelancers. Ask for references and contact them. Also ask for a photo ID and do not send a payment to anyone but them. This guy asked for a 1/2 deposit to hold the date. He spoke to me on the phone and through text many times and speaks as an experienced cameraman man. 

This person's supposed name is Steve Carter. He has a website listed and sends links to his prior work. 

Again never send funds to someone without real reference!

items.text:
Hi there, I’m a second year film student at METU directing a short scene for a class looking for a male actor! 

Longline: A relationship between a couple has reached its breaking point. However there is no hatred or malice between them, only a strong connection, pure love, and a melancholy understanding that they can no longer be together. 

Characters

Daisy is the female protagonist,  the scene mainly follows her view of her relationship with her long time partner Oliver. Daisy is a young adult photographer living with her partner who she deeply loves. 

Oliver is an accountant for a mid tier firm and is Daisys long time partner. They are not married but have been together for two years and he loves her deeply. After a serious disagreement between them the night before, he decides he can no longer be with Daisy despite feeling immense love for her. There is no malice or hatred, just release. 

Looking for an actor, playing age 20-25, to fill the male part

Date: 4th November

Location: Near Oktogon 

Time: 9:30-17:30

Compensation: Not paid (as it is a student project) but food and drinks will be provided 

Final film will be shared with the cast so it can be used for showreels or acting material. 

If you’re interested please reach out!☺️

Either through dm or email at kaliste.rodi@gmail.com

items.text:
Hallo👋🏻 Wir suchen für unser neues No- Budget- Serien- Projekt noch EINE hobbymäßige SCHAUSPIELERIN (w/d) für unser neues Projekt! Es wird später noch ein Buch zur Staffel geben.

Titel: Siegerlandchaos Staffel 2: Traumawut + Abschlussepisode: Untergangseuphorie 

Genre: Krimi mit Fantasy- Elementen, Drama 

Logline:
Der Fokus liegt auf Lea, welche lernen muss, mit ihrem Trauma umzugehen, und dabei sowohl eine zerstörerische als auch versöhnliche Seite an sich entdeckt. Außerdem stellen sich die Fragen, was in Zukunft aus Sherlock Wickels Detektei werden soll und wer ein echtes oder ein falsches Spiel spielt. 

Zusammenfassung
Ausgangspunkt: Bei einem tragischen Ereignis verliert Lea ihre Ehefrau Maja, sowie so ziemlich alles, was ihr etwas bedeutet. Es stellen sich die Fragen, ob Maja noch lebt oder nicht, und wo der Verantwortliche für das Drama steckt. Lea gelangt langsam aber sicher an ihr Limit, während Sherlock Wickel sie im Stich zu lassen scheint. 

Konflikt: Es gibt mehrere Konflikte. Eine Psychiatrie sollte Ben Saalfeld heilen, aber verdarb ihn, Aufgrund der Umstände. Rache möchte er an Sherlock Wickel, Markus Wattson und insbesondere Lea nehmen. Hilfe bekommt er dabei von Sarahs Erzfeind Ludwig, beruhend auf Gegenseitigkeit. Ludwig möchte mit Jacks Kette, Sarah und Maja einen moralisch zwiespältigen Plan umsetzen, um sich selbst von Auswirkungen seiner Schuld zu befreien. Gleichzeitig geht es innerhalb seiner Organisation ebenfalls nicht mit rechten Dingen zu. 

Auflösung: Am Ende erhält Lea wichtige Erkenntnisse über 's sich selbst Verzeihen. Die Organisation wird überführt und die Detektei geschlossen. Es gibt Versöhnungen, Happy Ends und Drama. Maja, Emmas bzw. Jillians Eltern, Ludwig, Liora und Ben werden sterben. Sherlock Wickel und Lea lernen, das Glück in kleinen Momenten zu sehen. 

Stimmung: Intensiv, düster, humorvoll, spannend, mysteriös, actiongeladen, nah an realen Erfahrungen mit Traumata 

Besonders geeignet für Menschen, die sich tiefer mit Gefühlen auseinandersetzen möchten. 

Das Drehbuch enthält 125 Seiten, wovon bereits 11 gedreht wurden. Gedreht wird vermutlich wie gewohnt in Plittershagen (Freudenberg, NRW, nahe Siegen) und einem noch unbekannten Drehort als Leas zu Hause. Es sind ggf. Hunde vor Ort, weshalb Tierliebhaber erwünscht sind :) Fahrtkosten können leider nicht übernommen werden, aber für Spaß, Speis und Trank ist natürlich gesorgt😊

Ziel des Projekts: Wir möchten mit einer packenden Geschichte die Leute dazu bewegen, darüber nachzudenken, wer sie denn eigentlich wirklich sind. Außerdem wollen wir beim Dreh mehr Erfahrung sammeln, uns Qualitativ im Vergleich zu Staffel 1 massivst steigern und die 'Jack'- Timeline meiner Geschichten beenden. 

Wenn alle einverstanden sind, würde ich nach Möglichkeit gerne im Winter mit dem Dreh weitermachen. Diesmal stehe ich auf jeden Fall, im Gegensatz zu bei Mafialiebe, komplett zu Story, Handlung und Co. Ich finde, diese Geschichte bietet einen bestmöglichen Abschluss für die Reihe 'Siegerlandchaos' und ich würde mich sehr freuen, wenn wir das dann zusammen und in besserer Qualität hinkriegen 😊 Da das Drehbuch auch um Einiges kürzer und auf weniger Charakter- Konstellationen beschränkt ist, gehe ich auch von einer schnelleren Umsetzungsmöglichkeit als bei Staffel 1: Mafialiebe aus. Drehtage würden diesmal nach Möglichkeit komplett danach ausgerichtet, wer an welchem Tag nach Absprache Zeit hat. 

Veröffentlicht soll die 2. Staffel mitsamt Bonusepisode ebenfalls auf YouTube werden. 

Gesuchte Rollen:

Luna Drews - Spielalter 20-30 (w/d) - 1 Drehtag - freundlich, fürsorglich, zuhörend, lebensfroh, ernst, heimlich schwanger, blonde Haare 

Bereits 12 Darsteller*innen + 2 Hunde sind Teil des Teams. Die Truppe scheint ganz lustig zu sein und einige Mitglieder kenne ich auch schon länger.

Zusätzlich suchen wir einen neuen Drehort für Leas und Majas zu Hause. 

Ich suche keine Leute, die sagen: Ja, mach ich mal mit. Ich suche Leute, die sagen: Ja, das wäre voll cool, dabei zu sein! 

Wenn Interesse besteht, meldet euch gerne bei mir :)
jappycreations@gmail.com 

Zu mir: Ich bin Sarah Marie Schäfer, geb. am 01.10.2003 in Siegen, und wohne aktuell in der Nähe von Siegen in einem kleinen Dorf. Nach dem ich meinem verstorbenen Hund Jack versprach, meine Pläne in die Tat umzusetzen und glücklich zu werden, tat ich dies mit dem Beginn meines ersten Serienprojekts, das abgeschlossen wurde. Fortan spielte ich auch Theater und schloss einige andere Pläne ab. In der Schauspielerei habe ich meinen Weg gefunden und möchte diesen weitergehen. Trotz vieler Hürden, wie Autismus, Transidentität und einigen gesundheitlichen Problemen gebe ich nicht so schnell auf und bleibe an meinen Plänen dran.

Anbei sind ein paar Szenen aus Staffel 1 Folge 8 als Vorgeschmack :)

items.summary:
Hallo👋🏻 Wir suchen für unser neues No- Budget- Serien- Projekt noch EINE hobbymäßige SCHAUSPIELERIN (w/d) für unser neues Projekt! Es wird später noch ein Buch zur Staffel geben.

Titel: Siegerlandchaos Staffel 2: Traumawut + Abschlussepisode: Untergangseuphorie 

Genre: Krimi mit Fantasy- Elementen, Drama 

Logline:
Der Fokus liegt auf Lea, welche lernen muss, mit ihrem Trauma umzugehen, und dabei sowohl eine zerstörerische als auch versöhnliche Seite an sich entdeckt. Außerdem stellen sich die Fragen, was in Zukunft aus Sherlock Wickels Detektei werden soll und wer ein echtes oder ein falsches Spiel spielt. 

Zusammenfassung
Ausgangspunkt: Bei einem tragischen Ereignis verliert Lea ihre Ehefrau Maja, sowie so ziemlich alles, was ihr etwas bedeutet. Es stellen sich die Fragen, ob Maja noch lebt oder nicht, und wo der Verantwortliche für das Drama steckt. Lea gelangt langsam aber sicher an ihr Limit, während Sherlock Wickel sie im Stich zu lassen scheint. 

Konflikt: Es gibt mehrere Konflikte. Eine Psychiatrie sollte Ben Saalfeld heilen, aber verdarb ihn, Aufgrund der Umstände. Rache möchte er an Sherlock Wickel, Markus Wattson und insbesondere Lea nehmen. Hilfe bekommt er dabei von Sarahs Erzfeind Ludwig, beruhend auf Gegenseitigkeit. Ludwig möchte mit Jacks Kette, Sarah und Maja einen moralisch zwiespältigen Plan umsetzen, um sich selbst von Auswirkungen seiner Schuld zu befreien. Gleichzeitig geht es innerhalb seiner Organisation ebenfalls nicht mit rechten Dingen zu. 

Auflösung: Am Ende erhält Lea wichtige Erkenntnisse über 's sich selbst Verzeihen. Die Organisation wird überführt und die Detektei geschlossen. Es gibt Versöhnungen, Happy Ends und Drama. Maja, Emmas bzw. Jillians Eltern, Ludwig, Liora und Ben werden sterben. Sherlock Wickel und Lea lernen, das Glück in kleinen Momenten zu sehen. 

Stimmung: Intensiv, düster, humorvoll, spannend, mysteriös, actiongeladen, nah an realen Erfahrungen mit Traumata 

Besonders geeignet für Menschen, die sich tiefer mit Gefühlen auseinandersetzen möchten. 

Das Drehbuch enthält 125 Seiten, wovon bereits 11 gedreht wurden. Gedreht wird vermutlich wie gewohnt in Plittershagen (Freudenberg, NRW, nahe Siegen) und einem noch unbekannten Drehort als Leas zu Hause. Es sind ggf. Hunde vor Ort, weshalb Tierliebhaber erwünscht sind :) Fahrtkosten können leider nicht übernommen werden, aber für Spaß, Speis und Trank ist natürlich gesorgt😊

Ziel des Projekts: Wir möchten mit einer packenden Geschichte die Leute dazu bewegen, darüber nachzudenken, wer sie denn eigentlich wirklich sind. Außerdem wollen wir beim Dreh mehr Erfahrung sammeln, uns Qualitativ im Vergleich zu Staffel 1 massivst steigern und die 'Jack'- Timeline meiner Geschichten beenden. 

Wenn alle einverstanden sind, würde ich nach Möglichkeit gerne im Winter mit dem Dreh weitermachen. Diesmal stehe ich auf jeden Fall, im Gegensatz zu bei Mafialiebe, komplett zu Story, Handlung und Co. Ich finde, diese Geschichte bietet einen bestmöglichen Abschluss für die Reihe 'Siegerlandchaos' und ich würde mich sehr freuen, wenn wir das dann zusammen und in besserer Qualität hinkriegen 😊 Da das Drehbuch auch um Einiges kürzer und auf weniger Charakter- Konstellationen beschränkt ist, gehe ich auch von einer schnelleren Umsetzungsmöglichkeit als bei Staffel 1: Mafialiebe aus. Drehtage würden diesmal nach Möglichkeit komplett danach ausgerichtet, wer an welchem Tag nach Absprache Zeit hat. 

Veröffentlicht soll die 2. Staffel mitsamt Bonusepisode ebenfalls auf YouTube werden. 

Gesuchte Rollen:

Luna Drews - Spielalter 20-30 (w/d) - 1 Drehtag - freundlich, fürsorglich, zuhörend, lebensfroh, ernst, heimlich schwanger, blonde Haare 

Bereits 12 Darsteller*innen + 2 Hunde sind Teil des Teams. Die Truppe scheint ganz lustig zu sein und einige Mitglieder kenne ich auch schon länger.

Zusätzlich suchen wir einen neuen Drehort für Leas und Majas zu Hause. 

Ich suche keine Leute, die sagen: Ja, mach ich mal mit. Ich suche Leute, die sagen: Ja, das wäre voll cool, dabei zu sein! 

Wenn Interesse besteht, meldet euch gerne bei mir :)
jappycreations@gmail.com 

Zu mir: Ich bin Sarah Marie Schäfer, geb. am 01.10.2003 in Siegen, und wohne aktuell in der Nähe von Siegen in einem kleinen Dorf. Nach dem ich meinem verstorbenen Hund Jack versprach, meine Pläne in die Tat umzusetzen und glücklich zu werden, tat ich dies mit dem Beginn meines ersten Serienprojekts, das abgeschlossen wurde. Fortan spielte ich auch Theater und schloss einige andere Pläne ab. In der Schauspielerei habe ich meinen Weg gefunden und möchte diesen weitergehen. Trotz vieler Hürden, wie Autismus, Transidentität und einigen gesundheitlichen Problemen gebe ich nicht so schnell auf und bleibe an meinen Plänen dran.

Anbei sind ein paar Szenen aus Staffel 1 Folge 8 als Vorgeschmack :)

# **🎥 Casting Call! **

​

Wir suchen vier Darsteller:innen für einen Messefilm in Düsseldorf!

Gedreht wird am 17. & 18. November auf der Messe Düsseldorf sowie an weiteren Terminen im November an passenden Locations.

​

Hier alle Rollen im Überblick:

​

👨 Arzt / Ärztin (40–55 Jahre)

Seriös, sympathisch und authentisch.

Dein zusätzlicher Drehtag ist am 14. November.

​

👩 Frau mit Migrationshintergrund / Start-up-Darstellerin (30–35 Jahre)

Modern, kommunikativ und selbstbewusst.

Zusätzlicher Drehtag: 5. November – kurzer Vorab-Dreh.

​

👩 Pflegekraft (25–35 Jahre)

Einfühlsam, natürlich und offen.

Zusätzlicher Drehtag: 22. oder 29. November (nach Absprache)

​

👨‍🔬 Forscher:in / Wissenschaftsbereich (30–40 Jahre)

Professionell, ruhig und fokussiert.

Zusätzlicher Drehtag: 22. oder 29. November (nach Absprache)

​

📍 Drehorte: Messe Düsseldorf + thematisch passende Arbeitsumgebungen

📅 Drehtage: 5., 14., 17., 18., 22. oder 29. November (je nach Rolle)

💶 Gage: 300 € pro Drehtag → insgesamt 900 € pro Person

​

Wenn du Lust auf ein professionelles, sympathisches Team und eine spannende Produktion hast, kommentiere einfach „Info“ 👇

​

Dann schicken wir dir den Bewerbungslink mit allen weiteren Details!

items.text:
# **CASTING CALL** (english version below)

Hey, wir suchen Schauspieler*innen für unseren Low-Budget-Studenten-Kurzfilm. Bei Interesse kontaktiert uns bitte per E-Mail: **[LivShortfilm2026@gmail.com](mailto:LivShortfilm2026@gmail.com)**.

Der Film wird an verschiedenen Locations gedreht, daher solltet ihr über einen längeren Zeitraum (**mindestens eine Woche am Stück**) verfügbar sein. 

**Unterkünfte, Anfahrt und Verpflegung werden gestellt.**

** **

** **
## **Gesucht wird:**

**weiblich gelesene Person (Sänger*in / Schauspieler*in)**

20-35 Jahre alt

**Voraussetzungen:**
* Musikalischer Hintergrund erforderlich (Sie sollten Gesangserfahrung und wenn möglich Erfahrung mit dem Klavier haben) 
* Autoführerschein
* Deutsche Sprache C1

 

**Männlich gelesene Person (Schauspieler*in)**

20-35 Jahre alt

**Voraussetzungen:**
* Autoführerschein
* Deutsche Sprache C1

 

**Drehtage:**

Anfang bis Mitte Januar

 

**Handlung:**

Die Sängerin Liv kämpft mit ihrer stagnierenden Karriere. Nachdem sie vor einem ihrer Auftritte zusammengebrochen ist, nimmt sie sich eine Auszeit mit ihrem Freund.

Während er glaubt, ihren Traum zu retten, versucht sie, sich von dem zu befreien, was aus diesem Traum geworden ist.

 

 

## **ENGLISH VERSION**

items.text:
Hello fellow Colorado actors. Many of you may not know that as a SAG member actors need to follow SAG rules. I have seen several violations of SAG rules, not only in our Denver market, but in New Mexico as well. Did you know that SAG rule 14 states:

A member cannot work as both a performer and a casting director, or a performer and a member of another theatrical teamster union, on the same production without the union's consent? 

Actors should not be casting directors due to a conflict of interest, as it can lead to biased decision-making in favor of their own acting career, and because the two roles require different skill sets. 

A casting director's job is to serve the production's needs by finding the best fit for a role, a process that requires a separate and objective perspective from the actor's self-interest in getting cast. 

If you know of anyone that is breaking SAG rule 14, I urge you to call or email SAG in Los Angeles and ask to speak with their violation’s department. You can also make the claim anonymously!￼

SAG-AFTRA / (855) 724-2387
info@sagaftra.org

The Uzual Suspects Casting Agency
About Us
The Uzual Suspects Casting Agency is a proudly South African-based casting and extras coordination agency, operating since 2018. We work behind the scenes to help bring incredible stories to life — connecting talent with opportunity across film, television, and digital productions.
Our Talent
With a growing database of over 1,000 talented actors, actresses, artists, and models, we take pride in representing individuals who continue to make us proud on some of the biggest local and international stages. Our artists have been featured in productions on Netflix, DStv, BET, and many more renowned platforms.
What We Do
We specialize in supplying background extras, featured roles, models, and performing artists for feature films, commercials, music videos, and television projects. Our experienced coordination team ensures every production finds the perfect fit for its creative vision.
Join Us
We’re growing fast — and The Uzual Suspects Casting Agency is the place to be if you’re passionate about building a career in the entertainment industry. Whether you’re new to the scene or a seasoned performer, we’d love to work with you.

Chętne osoby zapraszam do kontaktu na priv. Pozdrawiam.

items.text:
Hiya 👋🏽 We’re casting actors for a proof-of-concept short for our series about one woman’s search for “The One”! 

It’s like if The Mindy Project, Chewing Gum, and New Girl, and Crashing (2016) all had delusional love child!

We’re hoping to build a creative dream team—a film family we can create with long-term. Once this project is crowdfunded, cast and crew members who join now will be prioritized for the pilot (which will be paid) and the full series 🤞🏽

SUMMARY: We’ll follow hopeful romantic Mika through a series of meet-cutes, mess-ups, and missed connections. Sick of the bleak reality of dating in LA, she’s taking love into her own hands…and she’ll do anything to orchestrate the perfect romance.

This show is for the lovers and the cynics—a character-driven situational comedy that’s both a love letter and critique of the rom-coms that raised us. Crushed is about love, sex and the desire to connect, the fear of connection, and how far we’re willing to go for it. 

ROLES:
 • Mika (Lead, Female, Black, 20s–30s)

 • Jamie (Lead, Male, Any, 20s–30s)

 • K’hrystie (Female, Any, 20s–30s)

 • Hot Dog–Park Guy (Male, Any, 20s–30s)

Diverse actors of all experience levels welcome!

Dates: January 30th – February 1st, 2026 (2-3 day shoot)
Location: West LA / Ventura
Compensation: Unpaid (Passion Project) — meals + credit provided

Please submit to Casting@flyingjewelfilms.com with:

* ﻿﻿Headshot
* ﻿﻿Resume (if applicable, no experience necessary)
* ﻿﻿Reel (if available; not required for extras)
* ﻿﻿Role(s) you're submitting for
* ﻿﻿LA Local status & availability for shoot

Sides will be provided once you email your submission.

Thank you!!

items.text:
Part 4: When Paths Cross Again (final part)

It was one of those nights the city felt too familiar — the lights, the noise, even the way the air carried stories I wasn’t part of anymore.

I was leaving a café, half-lost in thought, when I heard a voice behind me. Soft. Careful.

> “You still take the long way home?”

I turned… and there she was.
Same eyes. Same calm that never needed words.

For a second, the city disappeared — no cars, no people, just silence between two souls who had already said goodbye once.

She smiled, gently.
I did too.

We didn’t hug. We didn’t speak.
We just stood there, letting time do what it does best — remind us that some stories never really end.

Then, just like before, the moment passed.
She turned to leave, and this time… I didn’t stop her.

Because maybe fate wasn’t giving us another turn — maybe it was just showing us we’d already taken it.

- Migo Palendrom write up

items.text:
🎤📀🎆✨CASTING CALL!!⭐️🌈🦄💋

We’re casting for Karaoke Club, a UBC student short film and we’d love to see your audition!

Make sure to review the details and character breakdown before sending in your submission & please spread the word to anyone who’d be interested!
✨
Project Details:
🎬 UBC Student Short Film
📅 Shoot Dates: March 6–8, 2026
🎭 Non-union, volunteer/unpaid
📍Metro Vancouver
✨
Submission Instructions:
Please send your self-tape and/or demo reel + headshot to KaraokeClubFilm@gmail.com
Include:
    •    Your name, height, location, and role(s) you’re interested in
    •    Confirmation that you’re 18+
    •    A short video of you singing 16 bars of a song 

🎤 Genres: Indie / Pop / Rock / Alternative (or any combo!)
Think vibes like Chappell Roan, The Beaches, Conan Gray, Boygenius, or K-Pop Demon Hunters — whatever best shows off your voice!
✨
Deadline: Please submit by November 7, 2025.
Submissions will remain open until December, but later entries may miss out on in-person audition or chemistry read opportunities.
✨🎶✨
We can’t wait to see your auditions and bring Karaoke Club to life!

Follow us on Instagram @karaokeclubfilm
❤️❤️❤️

items.text:
Short Film: “Adieu in Colours”

🎥 Written & Directed by Mitchell May

🎭 Genre: Emotional Drama / Art-House

📍 Filming Location: Bournemouth Beach

📅 Shoot Dates: Starts on 19th November

💰 Compensation: No compensation, but will be good for exposure

ROLE: DAVID (Lead, Male, 18–29)

David is a young man navigating the stages of grief after losing someone he loved.

This is a visually driven role — performance relies heavily on expression, silence, and body language rather than dialogue.

Traits:

Age: 18–29

Gender: Male

Open ethnicity

Emotionally open, introspective, strong nonverbal performer

Scenes include:

Joyful montage with partner (arcade & beach)

Emotional breakdown on the beach

Symbolic, visual scenes involving coloured balloons

Transformation from despair to peace

🎞️ Minimal dialogue — powerful, emotional storytelling through performance.

To Apply:

📩 Send Headshot, CV, and Showreel or self-tape to

👉 mitchellmay478@gmail.com

Subject: “DAVID — Adieu in Colours”

items.text: Hi actors! I'm trying to get into headshot photography professionally and I'm looking for people to help me practice, completely free of charge (obviously). I'm Nottingham based, and if you're Midlands based, or willing to travel, please get in touch 😄

attachments.ocrText: May be an image of one or more people
May be an image of one or more people, blonde hair and people smiling
May be an image of one or more people

topComments.text:
Hi!
That’s a great initiative — headshot photography is such an important and subtle craft. If you want to get into this genre professionally, I’d really recommend first studying actor headshots specifically.

An actor’s portrait isn’t just a pretty picture — it’s about capturing the actor’s type and their range in a single image. The eyes are the key: direct gaze into the lens, emotional presence, and clarity. Usually it’s framed from the shoulders up, sometimes slightly lower, with  grey background in studio, outdoors  or softly blurred natural tones or green tones.

Understanding how to see and reveal an actor’s essence is what makes a true headshot photographer. Wishing you all the best as you explore this field!
Hi I would be happy to help. I’m based in Nottinghamshire

items.text:
**CASTING CALL**
*Half-Day Social Media Shoot – Housing Association*

 

Hi everyone! 👋

 

We’re an independent media agency, looking for a small group of confident actors to feature in a short **half-day** filming project for a well-known **Housing Association**.

📍 **Location:** Welwyn Garden City

📅 **Date:** ASAP

⏱️ **Duration:** Half-day (approx. 4 hours)

💸 **Usage:** Digital Channels only 

🎥 **Style:** Natural, lifestyle content - showcasing everyday living and community vibes

 

We’re looking for:

✨ A diverse mix of people, ideally aged 30–45

✨ Comfortable on camera, relaxed and authentic energy (not a speaking part)

✨ Able to take light direction and have fun with it!

 

If you’re interested, please **comment below or drop me a message** with:

1️⃣ A recent headshot or link to your profile/portfolio 

2️⃣ Your location / ability to travel

3️⃣ Your availability W/C 3rd November

 

Feel free to tag anyone you think would suit this too! 🙌

 

Thanks so much - looking forward to connecting!

Conrad

topComments.text: Mentioned everything just not most important “payment”.

Kortfilmen Banana Ice søger skuespillere den 30. november i Svendborg!

Kortfilmen Banana Ice er støttet af Odense Filmværksted og søger 3 skuespillere til at være med den 29. og 30. november.

Filmen handler om Val, der på en bar får sat sit nye venskab til Rikke og Sika på prøve, da narkopolitiet dukker op til en razzia.

Bartender, Bettina: Kvinde i alderen 25-65 år. Skal være med ca. kl. 15-21. (Højst sandsynligt kun få timer i dette tidsrum). 

Politibetjente: Mænd i alderen 35-65. Skal være med den 30. november ca. kl. 15-21.  

Da filmen er en lavbudget produktion, er jobbet desværre ulønnet og vi prioriterer skuespillere der befinder sig i nærheden af Svendborg ifht. transportomkostninger. 

Der er fuld forplejning på optagelserne. 

Hvis dette har interesse, så send gerne en mail med billede og evt. showreel eller præsentationsvideo til juliagormsen@hotmail.com med emnefeltet: 
BANANA ICE - rollen du søger

topComments.text:
Unless it's a student production ALWAYS pay your cast and crew. Start a crowdfunding campaign, apply to advocacy groups that align with your film's message for grants, take out a personal bank loan, hold bake sales and car washes, meet with local/regional businesses for product placement.

Even Spike Lee, before he was "Spike Lee" got financing for his first film "She's Gotta Have It" when no one even knew who Spike Lee was..But STOP this practice of expecting Actors and Crew to work for free on your films.

What about liability insurance to cover the cast and crew on set? A film set is a place where a lot of incidents could happen. What if they get hurt on set? How are you going to compensate them for their medical expenses and lost work time? How are you going to cover equipment damaged or lost to such a situation? What if the property (house, offices, vase, etc. ) gets damaged, how are you going to cover those expenses?

What about a completion bond to insure the film is finished or pay the people for their time if it's not? Do you have that? 

My point is you have to start treating your business as a BUSINESS and stop expecting cast and crew to work for free. Filmmaking isn't just shooting footage on set and cutting it together in post. Part of filmmaking is finding the funding to make a film. And if you don't want to do that legwork then you don't really want to be in the film industry.

topComments.text:
Unless it's a student production ALWAYS pay your cast and crew. Start a crowdfunding campaign, apply to advocacy groups that align with your film's message for grants, take out a personal bank loan, hold bake sales and car washes, meet with local/regional businesses for product placement.

Even Spike Lee, before he was "Spike Lee" got financing for his first film "She's Gotta Have It" when no one even knew who Spike Lee was..But STOP this practice of expecting Actors and Crew to work for free on your films.

What about liability insurance to cover the cast and crew on set? A film set is a place where a lot of incidents could happen. What if they get hurt on set? How are you going to compensate them for their medical expenses and lost work time? How are you going to cover equipment damaged or lost to such a situation? What if the property (house, offices, vase, etc. ) gets damaged, how are you going to cover those expenses?

What about a completion bond to insure the film is finished or pay the people for their time if it's not? Do you have that? 

My point is you have to start treating your business as a BUSINESS and stop expecting cast and crew to work for free. Filmmaking isn't just shooting footage on set and cutting it together in post. Part of filmmaking is finding the funding to make a film. And if you don't want to do that legwork then you don't really want to be in the film industry.

items.text:
**014  Mini serial  wojenny 1940 –  Przyjaciel ojca głównej bohaterki (mężczyzna )**

 

**Szukamy skarbu Templariuszy!**

 

Nasza Gliwicka Grupa Pasjonatów **‘’Grupa1940’’ **poszukuje mężczyzny  do roli przyjaciela ojca głównej bohaterki. Najlepiej jakby kandydat miała **od 40 – 50 lat** ** bez żadnych tatuaży na twarzy czy rękach oraz farbowanych włosach oraz zarostu na twarzy. **Prosimy też o wysłanie aktualnych zdjęć. Postać pojawi się w pierwszym odcinku projektu jako więzień a potem razem z Antonim, jego przyjacielem zostaną zabici przez Niemców. Planujemy również zrobić osobną sesję z tymi bohaterami i wywołać zdjęcie jako jeden z gadżetów projektu. Szukamy kogoś z Gliwic lub okolic: Zabrze, Katowice najdalej.  Przed zdjęciami głównymi, planujemy też wykonać sesje testowe i przymiarowe dla poszczególnych aktorów i aktorek. Same zdjęcia będą realizowane na terenie Gliwic.  Przedstawione powyżej materiały są z naszych sesji testowych.

 

     **Prosimy o wysłanie aktualnych zdjęć** gdyż tylko takowe zgłoszenia będą rozpatrywane. Szukamy kogoś z Gliwic lub okolic: Zabrze, Katowice najdalej gdyż odległość do tej roli ma znaczenie, jest to ważny czynnik w wyborze kandydata jak również doświadczenie aktorskie ( nie koniecznie duże ). Same zdjęcia będą realizowane na terenie Gliwic.

 

**Na wiosnę roku 2026 planujemy realizacje zdjęc do tego **projektu. Będziemy realizować mini serial oparty o wątki grupy okultystycznej ’’**Ahnenerbe’**’ która chce zdobyć słynne artefakty ale w tym ktoś im chce przeszkadzać. Będziemy też sukcesywnie dodawać inne ogłoszenia związane z tym projektem. Mile widziane zdjęcia aktualne. Na zdjęciu powyżej osoba będzie mieć podobny kostium.** **Umieszczone materiały są z naszej sesji.** Nie będzie to zlecenie płatne.**

 

Od 01.04.25 założyliśmy swój kanał na portalu youtube z filmami z naszych planów żeby można było zobaczyć jak to u nas wygląda od kuchni. 

 

https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCE8KyfwpyFGzzwUDqdwy74g

 

Więcej informacji na Priv

** **

**Serial nie jest stworzony z sympatii do tej nazistowskiej organizacji lecz wynika to z samego scenariusza aby ukazał zbrodnie i sam fakt iż była w pełni zła. W produkcji znajdą się osoby, które będą chcieć walczyć i potępiać te wielkie zło jakim był nazizm. W oparciu o Dz.U.2017.0.2204 t.j. - Ustawa z dnia 6 czerwca 1997 r. - Kodeks karny,Art. 256 "Propagowanie faszyzmu lub innego ustroju totalitarnego lub nawoływanie domnienawiści", §3 - nie narusza prawa proponując przedmiot do celów historycznych lub kolekcjonerskich.**

**Mini serial  wojenny 1940 – Szukamy 3 pań do roli statystek francuskich**

 

Nasza Gliwicka Grupa Pasjonatów **‘’Grupa1940’’** poszukuje kobiet do roli statystek francuskich obywatelek. Kobiety wystąpią w jednym z odcinków kiedy to niemieccy żołnierze napadają na miasto francuskie.  Przewidujemy wcześniej kilka sesji testowych. Scena ataku planowana jest gdzieś w okolicy lipca lub sierpnia. Na pewno poszukujemy osób od 18 roku życia, nie ma granicy wieku do ilu lat. items.text:
Part 3: Echoes of What Was

Days turned into weeks, yet the memory of that night refused to fade.
Every corner of the city seemed to hum with her voice — faint, distant, but alive.

I’d catch myself glancing at passing faces, searching for her shadow in reflections.
The coffee shop we once sat in. The bridge where we said too much and too little.
Everything still carried a trace.

But life doesn’t stop for memories.
One evening, as the city began to glow again, I met someone new — or maybe she found me.
She wasn’t trying to replace the past… just remind me that I still had a future.

Her laughter was softer, her silence warmer.
And for the first time, I didn’t feel the urge to look back.

Still, sometimes… when the streetlights flicker just right,
I swear I hear her whisper —

> “If fate gives us another turn…”

And in that moment, I smile.
Because deep down, I know fate isn’t done yet.

- Migo Palendrom- write up

I’m an actor, ultra runner, martial artist, and performance coach based in Washington. My background is in endurance sports, Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu, and teaching mind–body–spirit discipline through my brand Northwest Elite Spirit.

I bring a controlled, physical presence and real fighting ability to camera work — everything from disciplined mentor roles to intense action or dramatic scenes. I’m used to performing under pressure, training daily, and working both solo and in team environments.

Open to short films, independent projects, commercials, and cinematic collaborations that value authenticity, focus, and movement.

If you’re looking for someone who can combine physical precision, calm intensity, and emotional depth, let’s connect.

📍 Based in WA — available to travel.

🎥 YouTube & IG: @NorthwestEliteSpirit

Short Film: “Adieu in Colours”

🎥 Written & Directed by Mitchell May

🎭 Genre: Emotional Drama / Art-House

📍 Filming Location: Bournemouth Beach

📅 Shoot Dates: Starts on 19th November

💰 Compensation: No compensation, but will be good for exposure

ROLE: DAVID (Lead, Male, 18–29)

David is a young man navigating the stages of grief after losing someone he loved.

This is a visually driven role — performance relies heavily on expression, silence, and body language rather than dialogue.

Traits:

Age: 18–29

Gender: Male

Open ethnicity

Emotionally open, introspective, strong nonverbal performer

Scenes include:

Joyful montage with partner (arcade & beach)

Emotional breakdown on the beach

Symbolic, visual scenes involving coloured balloons

Transformation from despair to peace

🎞️ Minimal dialogue — powerful, emotional storytelling through performance.

To Apply:

📩 Send Headshot, CV, and Showreel or self-tape to

👉 mitchellmay478@gmail.com

Subject: “DAVID — Adieu in Colours”

We're casting for our magical Tanfield Railway Christmas Experience in County Durham– and we’re on the lookout for charismatic, professional Christmas Elves to join the team!

📍 Location: Tanfield Railway Path, Newcastle upon Tyne NE16 5ET
📆 Contract: November – December 2025
💸 Rate: £14 per hour — Pay & Half on Christmas Eve

✨ Requirements:

• Entry-level acting skills

• Immersive performance ability

• Must absolutely love Christmas!

You’ll be part of a heartwarming festive experience for families and children, working alongside our Santa and Train Conductor in a beautifully themed setting.

🧝‍♀️ We’re looking for:

• Confident, energetic performers with great improvisation skills

• Friendly, reliable team players

• Previous experience working with children or in character-based roles is a plus

📌 Important Info:

• Costume and full training provided

• Paid rehearsals and site visits will be scheduled in early November – exact dates TBC

• Below is the confirmed list of working dates, and shift times :

sharedPost.text:
With Christmas just around the corner...

"Get ready to find your voice and amplify your confidence with PBL Voiceover Coach! With hundreds of clients under our belt, our expert team has helped everyone from beginners to seasoned pros land their dream voiceover gigs. From commercials to cartoons, video games to corporate videos, our clients have gone on to voice projects that have taken them to a new level. 

At PBL Voiceover Coach, we're passionate about empowering voiceover artists to develop their unique sound and style. Our masterclasses are designed to give you the skills, confidence, and industry insights you need to succeed in the competitive world of voiceovers.

PBL Voiceover Coach is excited to also announce that  partnering with special guests for every full-day participant, giving you a unique opportunity to learn from industry experts. You'll get to hear from some of the most successful people working in the voiceover industry, gaining valuable insights and advice to help you succeed. In Dublin, Galway and Cork this 2026.

As a full-day participant, you'll also receive a professional voiceover demo to help you kick-start your career. Our masterclasses are designed to equip you with the skills and confidence you need to land your dream voiceover gig.

Don't just take our word for it - our social media accounts are filled with glowing testimonials from past students who've gone on to achieve great things in the industry. Ready to take the next step? Book your spot now at pblvoiceover.com 

Join us in 2026 for our PBL Voiceover Masterclasses and discover how to:

- Develop a unique and compelling voice style
- Master the art of voiceover technique and performance
- Create a standout demo reel that gets noticed
- Navigate the business side of the industry like a pro
- Land your first (or next) voiceover gig

We  have years of experience in the industry and will guide you every step of the way. Don't miss out on this opportunity to take your voiceover career to the next level. Sign up for our 2026 masterclasses and get ready to find your voice and make it heard!"

All it takes is a spark. Curious? Drop us a line to find out more or visit Pblvoiceover.com

KRAKÓW, TEATR NIEZALEŻNY

Szukam ludzi do spektaklu historyczno-poetyckiego, w stylu filmowym, epickim, opartym na życiorysach Tadeusza Borowskiego i Krzysztofa Kamila Baczyńskiego. Premiera przewidziana jest na marzec 2026 roku. Potrzebuję ludzi czujących epokę, poezję, niekoniecznie zawodowców. Poniżej lista postaci, do których szukam aktorów:
* Tadeusz (postać główna, pierwowzór - Tadeusz Borowski i Wincenty Gawron)
* Krzysztof (pierwowzór - K. K. Baczyński)
* Stary Doktor (pierwowzór - Janusz Korczak)
* Kapelan (pierwowzór - ksiądz Tiso)
* Bracia żydowscy Jakub i Izaak
* Roma (żona polskiego oficera)
* Pola (pierwowzór - Barbara Baczyńska)
* ''Święta'' (handlująca zrabowanymi kosztownościami)
* oficerowie hitlerowscy - Wolf i Jurgen

Chętne osoby zapraszam do kontaktu na priv. Pozdrawiam.

items.text:
CASTING CALL: Protesters Voiceover – “Denied Care” Series

Project Title: Denied Care
Production Company: Superstar TV Entertainment, Inc.
Type: Voiceover (Non-Union / Indie Production)
Location: Remote Recording Accepted
Compensation: paid 
Recording Date: November 15th

Looking for 3 voiceovers

---

PROJECT OVERVIEW

Denied Care is a scripted drama following Ava Winters, a young woman denied life-saving treatment by a broken healthcare system. The story exposes the real human cost of bureaucratic neglect through emotional, defiant, and darkly comedic storytelling.

Short Film feature a pivotal protest montage — where voices from across the nation rise in solidarity. This casting call is for those protester voices — raw, real, and unapologetic.

---

ROLE: PROTESTER VOICEOVER (MULTIPLE TALENTS)

Gender: Any
Age Range: 18–65
Accent: Open — diverse voices encouraged
Tone: Authentic, passionate, emotional, and real
Vocal Quality:

Gritty, tired, but determined

Feels like you’ve lived it — not “performed” it

Think real activists, not voice actors

Examples of Lines (for audition):

“We are not invisible!”

“You can’t deny care to the living!”

“We’re sick, not silent!”

“Every denial has a name!”

“We are the denied — and we’re not backing down!”

(Actors may be asked to record crowd-style chants, overlapping dialogue, and emotional reactions.)

---

RECORDING NOTES

Please record clean audio (WAV or MP3) with minimal background noise.

Multiple takes with varying energy levels are encouraged.

Shouting, chanting, and overlapping crowd energy welcome.

items.text:
Casting Call: Singer-Songwriter for Music Video (Unpaid)

Production Title: Christmas Music video 
Production Company: Superstar TV Entertainment Inc.
Type: Music Video
Location: Colorado (exact location TBD)
Filming Dates: late November early December 2025
Compensation: Unpaid (Copy, Credit, and Meals Provided)

---

About the Project

Superstar TV Entertainment Inc. is producing a heartfelt, cinematic music video featuring a singer-songwriter whose performance captures raw emotion and authenticity. This project is designed to highlight both the artist and visual storytelling — similar in tone to Lewis Capaldi, Adele, or Noah Kahan.

The final video will be professionally shot and released across Superstar TV platforms, YouTube, and social media for maximum exposure.

---

Roles

🎤 Lead Artist / Singer-Songwriter (Principal Role)

Gender: Open to all

Age Range: 18–35

Vocal Style: Pop, acoustic, R&B, soul, or indie-folk preferred

Description: Emotionally expressive performer with on-camera presence. Must be comfortable lip-syncing to playback or performing live vocals. Guitar or piano ability is a plus.

Requirements: Must be reliable, punctual, and open to creative collaboration.

---

Supporting Roles (If applicable)

Love Interest: Ages 20–35, expressive and able to convey emotional connection.

Extras: Audience members, friends, or background talent for performance scenes.

---

Compensation

Unpaid (Copy, Credit, and Meals Provided)

You’ll receive:

A professional-quality music video for your reel

IMDB credit under Superstar TV Entertainment Inc.

Networking opportunity for future paid productions

---

Submission Instructions

Please submit the following to tyler.schachtceo@outlook.com with the subject line:
Christmas Music Video – [Your Name]”

Include:

Headshot or clear photo

Short performance clip or demo reel (YouTube or social media link accepted)

Short bio or resume

Contact information (email + phone number)

🎬 **CASTING CALL – DENVER, CO!** 🎬

Hey everyone! I’m **casting for my upcoming web series, *****A Fish Outta Water*****,** and I’m looking for **3 Black women (ages 18–24)** in the **Denver area** to join this heartfelt and hilarious coming-of-age project 🐟💙

This is a **student-led production** created through my business, **Films On Mars LLC**, and we’ll be filming locally in **January 2026!**

✨ All character breakdowns, role details, and submission info are posted on my socials below —
INSTAGRAM 👉 @/a_fish_outta_water_
TIKTOK 👉 @/a_fish_outta_water

If you have any questions, feel free to **email me at** 📧 **FilmsOnMars@gmail.com**

This is such a special project to me — and I’d love to work with talented, passionate actors ready to tell a story that’s raw, funny, and real 🎥💫

Here’s a link to the audition form 👉 https://forms.gle/TzTnwqVp3Grm2eEA8

Please share this post to help spread the word! 🙌

#CastingCall #DenverActors #studentfilmmakers #IndieFilm #afishouttawater

items.text:
Statister søges i Vejle/Horsens 📹✨

Tidligere optagelser blev aflyst, så jeg søger igen statister til at medvirke i lidt video i Vejle/Horsens fredag den 7. november.

𝗛𝘃𝗲𝗺 𝘀ø𝗴𝗲𝗿 𝗷𝗲𝗴:

Jeg søger to "familier". 

Familie 1: En mand og en kvinde, der kan passe til en børnefamilie. Hertil også en-to børn. 

Familie 2: Et mere "modent" par (mand og kvinde) samt en eventuel hund.

OBS! Ingen store, synlige tatoveringer eller lignende. 

𝗣𝗿𝗮𝗸𝘁𝗶𝘀𝗸 𝗶𝗻𝗳𝗼: 
📍 Optagelserne foregår i Vejle eller Horsens.

🗓️ Fredag den 7. november. Enten kl. 9.30-12.00 eller 13.00-15.00. Det aftales nærmere.

💸 Jobbet betales med gavekort på 500 kr. pr mand. 

💌 Send en mail til jdk@miltonhuse.dk med billeder af dig/jer. Henvendelser på Facebook eller andre steder besvares IKKE. 

Obs! Optagelserne skal bruges til annoncering på Metas samt andre digitale platforme til et typehusfirma. Der er tale om flere klip af et hverdagsliv i et af vores udstillingshuse.

items.text:
In diesem Essay-Vlog untersuche ich die überraschenden Parallelen zwischen Claude Chabrols „Juste avant la nuit“ und der deutschen Kultserie „Derrick“.

Auf den ersten Blick zwei Welten – französischer Autorenfilm vs. deutscher Fernsehkrimi. Doch unter der Oberfläche offenbaren sie eine verblüffend ähnliche Seele: Schuld, Schweigen, moralischer Verfall und die stille Tragödie des Bürgertums.

https://youtu.be/ckhlxbK-jkI

#ChabrolLovers #Derrick #JochenHorst #FilmEssay #EuropeanCinema #PsychologicalDrama #ClaudeChabrol #DerrickAnalysis #70sCinema #Cinephile #GermanTelevision #ArtOfSilence #SlowCinema #Filmphilosophie

🎶Offering Free Acting Coachings for All Levels!🎶

Hi! I'm Colleen and I'm a private voice & acting teacher, and the owner of Virtuoso Studios. We are currently offering free VIRTUAL lessons to meet new students who may be interested in continuing professional individualized coaching!

We currently offer lessons in voice, piano, violin, viola, cello, guitar, and acting, along with 2 in-person recitals each year in 4 Midwestern states. Each of our teachers is committed to providing personalized instruction to help every student reach their goals. Whether you’re preparing for auditions, trying to book professional gigs, or simply looking to grow as a performer, our teachers are here to support and encourage you every step of the way!

If you’d like to get started, fill out this form, and we’ll match you with the teacher who’s the best fit for your goals and interests. [www.virtuosostudios.org/free-trial-lessons](https://www.virtuosostudios.org/free-trial-lessons)

Don’t forget to grab your tickets!

Georgetown Little Theatre proudly presents ***A Telling of The Christmas Carol*** — running **November 27th to December 6th, 2025**.

This isn’t your average Christmas Carol… it’s a witty, fast-paced, and heartfelt reimagining of the holiday classic. Ebenezer Scrooge still faces ghosts, regrets, and redemption, but along the way you’ll be treated to:
Laughs, Ghosts who bicker like overworked employees, Marley fumbling through haunting “protocols” And the timeless spirit of generosity and hope.

You might laugh, you might cry — but one thing is certain: you’ll have a fantastic time!

**62% sold out! — don’t wait!** 

Support local theatre
Support our amazing performers
Support the arts in our community

Tickets are on sale now — get yours before they’re gone!

georgetownlittletheatre.ca

# **🎥 Casting Call! **

​

Wir suchen vier Darsteller:innen für einen Messefilm in Düsseldorf!

Gedreht wird am 17. & 18. November auf der Messe Düsseldorf sowie an weiteren Terminen im November an passenden Locations.

​

Hier alle Rollen im Überblick:

​

👨 Arzt / Ärztin (40–55 Jahre)

Seriös, sympathisch und authentisch.

Dein zusätzlicher Drehtag ist am 14. November.

​

👩 Frau mit Migrationshintergrund / Start-up-Darstellerin (30–35 Jahre)

Modern, kommunikativ und selbstbewusst.

Zusätzlicher Drehtag: 5. November – kurzer Vorab-Dreh.

​

👩 Pflegekraft (25–35 Jahre)

Einfühlsam, natürlich und offen.

Zusätzlicher Drehtag: 22. oder 29. November (nach Absprache)

​

👨‍🔬 Forscher:in / Wissenschaftsbereich (30–40 Jahre)

Professionell, ruhig und fokussiert.

Zusätzlicher Drehtag: 22. oder 29. November (nach Absprache)

​

📍 Drehorte: Messe Düsseldorf + thematisch passende Arbeitsumgebungen

📅 Drehtage: 5., 14., 17., 18., 22. oder 29. November (je nach Rolle)

💶 Gage: 300 € pro Drehtag → insgesamt 900 € pro Person

​

Wenn du Lust auf ein professionelles, sympathisches Team und eine spannende Produktion hast, kommentiere einfach „Info“ 👇

​

Dann schicken wir dir den Bewerbungslink mit allen weiteren Details!

Perks are still available! Grab a producer/actor perk on AMERICAN MOTHER. James Duval (INDEPENDENCE DAY, DONNIE DARKO, GONE IN 60 SECONDS, Greg Araki's TEEN APOCALYPSE trilogy) has joined the cast, alongside...
Taryn Manning (ORANGE IS THE NEW BLACK, CROSSROADS, HUSTLE & FLOW, 8 MILE, MEAN GIRLS, SONS OF ANARCHY, THE ITALIAN JOB, CLEVELAND ABDUCTION, COLD MOUNTAIN), Nichole Brown (Aisha from COBRA KAI, RAVEN'S HOME), Keith Coogan (ADVENTURES IN BABYSITTING, TOY SOLDIERS, JAY AND SILENT BOB REBOOT, DON'T TELL MOM THE BABYSITTER'S DEAD, COUSINS) and Noel G. (THE FAST AND THE FURIOUS, FURIOUS 7, TRAINING DAY, STREET KINGS, THE DARK KNIGHT RISES, HARSH TIMES, THE MULE, DRAGGED ACROSS CONCRETE).

All 5 of these actors have already wrapped, so they're definitely a part of the film (no dropping out due to scheduling conflicts, etc). Producers are currently speaking with about several more well known actors in hopes to nab at least 3 of them for the film (maybe 8-10 in total if we can get this campaign to $20k). Grab a producer and actor perk on the film at indiegogo. https://www.indiegogo.com/projects/american-mother#/

items.text:
Short Film: “Adieu in Colours”

🎥 Written & Directed by Mitchell May

🎭 Genre: Emotional Drama / Art-House

📍 Filming Location: Bournemouth Beach

📅 Shoot Dates: Starts on 19th November

💰 Compensation: No compensation, but will be good for exposure

ROLE: DAVID (Lead, Male, 18–29)

David is a young man navigating the stages of grief after losing someone he loved.

This is a visually driven role — performance relies heavily on expression, silence, and body language rather than dialogue.

Traits:

Age: 18–29

Gender: Male

Open ethnicity

Emotionally open, introspective, strong nonverbal performer

Scenes include:

Joyful montage with partner (arcade & beach)

Emotional breakdown on the beach

Symbolic, visual scenes involving coloured balloons

Transformation from despair to peace

🎞️ Minimal dialogue — powerful, emotional storytelling through performance.

To Apply:

📩 Send Headshot, CV, and Showreel or self-tape to

👉 mitchellmay478@gmail.com

Subject: “DAVID — Adieu in Colours”

items.text:
Casting call for a new series! 

Location: Studio City
Dates: Between November 16-19 (one day; most likely only needed for a few hours) 

We’re assembling a passionate and talented cast for the first shoot of a new original series. This project is being produced for social media distribution but filmed in a horizontal, cinematic format before post-production edits. These initial shoot days will serve as a proof of concept — designed to build audience traction and secure brand partnerships and sponsorship funding for future episodes. These two roles will evolve into regular paid opportunities for our core crew. 

Compensation:
$125 per day, copy, on-set meals (lunch + crafty), and hands-on experience with a full professional production crew — including cameras, lighting, and sound equipment. This is a great opportunity to expand your portfolio with high-quality material.

To Apply:
Please email partnerships@aurelianscollective.com with your headshot and resume/reel and we will send you the sides
 to tape. Thank you for your interest — we look forward to hearing from you!

https://m.imdb.com/title/tt38714186/
